						<div class="postbody">I think it was more, it only did 3 million, these did 5. No we not giving you money to make a sequel to a 3 million game when you could be making a sequel to a 5 million game. In that 3 million was so-so and a sequel has traditionally had less buy-in than the first making it less appealing.<br /><br />Reading the books though paints a very different story, it really was low cost and massive profits back in the early days. Space Invaders caused a shortage of 100yen coins. These days a C64 game does 1250 sales and 96% of iOS devs are jealous <img src="./images/smilies/icon_wink.gif" alt=";)" title="Wink" /></div>

